1S pass pass X pass pass pass
[BCFlags "1f"]
[RotationNote "Board 2, chOption: E, chBasis: E, basisKind:Declarer, nOption:1, nBasis: 1, nRot: 0, useStandardVul: true"]
[VersionToken "4a79a4556f66f088d177ce88293f7c99280457091f07a83d22d3a3fea54938b6"]
[Category "Partnership Bidding"]
[Difficulty "intermediate"]
[SkillPath "partnership_bidding/overcalls"]
[Student "S"]
{SOUTH obviously has to pass when EAST opens 1\S.

NORTH has a reasonable Takeout Double. She hopes SOUTH will name a suit and they can just 
play a partscore.

You should almost always bid when partner makes a Takeout Double. Almost always. This is the one time 
when you don't. SOUTH's \S are so good that he passes, converting the Takeout Double into a 
Penalty Double.}

